column2: A simple interface for editing natural photos with generative neural networks.

column5: message

Fix typo in BatchReNormLayer

Import oopsies. Should be fixed now.

Cleanup comments

Comment cleanup!

Add BatchReNorm and Efficient MDCLW Layers

Include my naive BatchReNorm implementation and the updated MDCLW weight
parameterization function for improved multiscale dilated conv blocks.

Add Subpixel Reshape Layer, Switch Subpixel Layer to Set_Subtensor

Set_subtensor appears to be about twice as fast as inc_subtensor in this
case. A simple benchmarking script is available in this gist:
https://gist.github.com/ajbrock/cc083da8c274ff25acdc318b3249b972

Add Subpixel Layer 1

Added my version of the subpixel layer making use of inc_subtensor
calls. Currently working on a version involving splits and reshapes.
Rename models to API, fix typo in API IAN class

Update GIFS

Update README Gifs to display properly

Update Readme

Update command explanation and add more GIFs.

Merge pull request #9 from dribnet/pics

Add pics/.gitignore

Add pics/.gitignore

This prevents crashes when the pics subdirectory is not present
and also hides outputs from git.

Merge pull request #8 from michaelrgb/saveNewGIM

Button to save new ground-truth image.

Tested and working on Windows; I might modify this a bit in a future release so that "Reset," "Update," and "Infer" have more clear functionality (I suspect they might be a bit confusing right now, which is my fault--I'll think on a fix.)

Merge pull request #6 from michaelrgb/master

Dont change color if Cancel pressed, and open with initial color.

Tested and working on my Windows machine.

Change Name of Ground Truth Update Button

I'm changing the name of this button to "Update" to reflect its functionality while still allowing it to fit compactly into the interface. Starting to feel like I need a UI/UX designer--will be accepting this pull request shortly.

Integrate plat interface and update Readme

Integrated the plat abstraction interface (in models.py) to make the
NPE.py file framework-independent. Updated the readme with a new splash
GIF.

Button to save new ground-truth image.

The masking technique means the output image is based off the original
ground-truth image. After an aesthetically pleasing change is made, such as
growing the length of the hair, a new ground-truth image must be saved and
the latent space recalculated before a different change is made such as
changing the hair color.
Dont change color if Cancel pressed, and open with initial color.

Add non-cuDNN Option

Removed cuDNN as a dependency by replacing the DeconvLayers with
appropriately sliced TransposedConv2DLayers, and moving around some
imports and explicit DNN calls. cuDNN use is still the default, but can
be easily switched off by editing line 64 of NPE.py to "dnn=False."

Some brief fixes, README update, and a pre-trained model.

Add pretrained model to repo with git-lfs.
Add another pretrained model with slightly more complexity (note that
this is different from the IAN architecture already uploaded, and
doesn't appear to be as suitable for use with the NPE as my slimmed down
version. I haven't been able to test it very well because my local GPU
can barely handle this model. Its sample quality appears to be higher,
but its reconstruction quality appears to be lower).
Fixed some unnecessary imports and keyerrors
Added MADE/IAF support to NPE.
Renamed l_latents to l_Z for consistency across models.
Found a bug in the MADE layer.

Added some comments, working on making the code more readable.
